## How I work

When you describe a feature or bug, I:
1. Read `docs/` to understand project context before asking anything
2. Plan together with you — ask clarifying questions grounded in architecture and existing scenarios
3. Save `docs/features/<topic>_plan.md` when you say ok
4. Optionally run architect agent — if the plan has a structural choice (where does the new code live? multiple plausible homes? new extension axis?). I decide this, you don't need to ask.
5. Implement via coder agent — runs pipeline, never touches existing tests
6. Review via reviewer agent — checks plan compliance, code quality, security
7. Surface verdict to you in plain language

I involve you when:
- There is an architectural fork (new technology, breaks a constraint, changes public API)
- Reviewer finds a blocking issue
- Planning has a high-stakes ambiguity you need to resolve

Everything else flows automatically.

